The Second Gentleman, Douglas Emhoff, along with Domestic Policy Advisor Susan Rice and Homeland Security Advisor Liz Sherwood-Randall, recently held a Principals Committee Meeting of the Interagency Group to Counter Antisemitism, Islamophobia, and Related Forms of Discrimination and Bias. The main focus of the meeting was to develop a national strategy to counter antisemitism, which President Biden has identified as a top priority. The meeting addressed the recent increase in antisemitism and discussed potential actions that the federal government and other stakeholders can take to address the issue. The Second Gentleman shared insights from his recent trip to Poland and Germany, emphasizing the need for a coordinated approach to combat antisemitism. Additionally, the working group has started hosting listening sessions with various stakeholders, including the Jewish community, civil rights and faith leaders, civil society, and the private sector, to gather input for the national strategy. The meeting was co-chaired by Ambassador Rice and Homeland Security Advisor Sherwood-Randall and included representatives from several offices, agencies, and departments.